 <sect1 id="sec.adm.docupdate.gm">
  <title>February 13, 2014 (Initial Release)</title>
  <!--state if new or updated, if applicable, add number of bug, fate,
   or doc comment for reference-->
  
  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Update to &ostack; Havana</term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      The &dash; and the command line chapter have been updated to the
      &ostack; Havana release on which &productname; 3 is based. This
      includes the following changes:
     </para>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Some categories have been added to the &dash;'s main screen, resulting
        in an update of the following section:
        <xref
         linkend="sec.adm.dash.intro.main"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The compute, memory, and storage capacity of some default flavors has
        slightly changed. For details, refer to
        <xref linkend="sec.adm.dash.flavors"
         /> or
        <xref linkend="sec.adm.cli.flavors"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem><para>There are more quota parameters available now. For
       details, refer to <xref linkend="sec.adm.dash.quotas"/> or <xref
       linkend="sec.adm.cli.quotas"/>.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>The following procedures have been added to reflect the new
        features of &ostack; &o_ident; v3 API that are now supported in
        &productname; &dash;: <xref linkend="pro.adm.dash.user.roles"/>,
         <xref linkend="pro.adm.dash.user.groups"/>, and <xref
         linkend="pro.adm.dash.user.groups.assign"/>.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem><para>It is now possible to modify flavors from the
       &productname; &dash;. For details, refer to <xref
       linkend="pro.adm.dash.flavors.modify"/>.</para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
     </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
